.\" Manpage for Simple Shell.
.\"
.TH man 1 "05 Dec 2023" "1.0" "shell man page"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- recreating the functionality of a basic shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fICOMMAND\fR\... [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
sh is a recreation of a simple shell, which prompts a user for input and executes commands based on that input. This simple shell works by searching the user's environment for the PATH, extracting that path, then searching along the path, comparing stored user input for executable commands stored in files.

.SH COMMANDS
.B
.IP exit
exit the simple shell environment
.B
.IP env
print the environmental variables for the current shell.
.B
.IP ls
list files in current directory
.B
.IP pwd
print working directory path
.SH USAGE
to use, run file and enter desired command when prompted.
.SH EXAMPLE
.TP
.B simple_shell ls -l
list contents of current directory in long format

.SH SEE ALSO
.B
.IP AUTHORS
Created by Cody Walenciak and Courtney Graham
